lizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":27,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth was born about 1355. She married Osbert de Mundeford III about 1380. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died about 1396, in Hockwold, Norfolk, England, at the age of 43."},"et":{"about 1355–about 1396":"umbes 1355–umbes 1396","1345–1396":"1345–1396","1381–1456":"1381–1456","1385–1463":"1385–1463","1390–1465":"1390–1465","1355–1396":"1355–1396","about 1390":"umbes 1390","about 1380":"umbes 1380","1385":"1385","1396":"1396","ca 1385":"umbes 1385","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1390":"1390","25 September 1381":"25. september 1381","1456":"1456","1345":"1345","1355":"1355","1465":"1465","1463":"1463","about 1355":"umbes 1355","about 1396":"umbes 1396","Hockwold, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Hockwold, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mundeford's Manor, Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mundeford's manor, Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hockwold, Norfolk, England":"Hockwold, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1355–about 1396":"noin 1355–noin 139